                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13920275" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2014 00:23:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can check this out by going to the Solr admin and trying to add a new SolrCore with all the defaults. Just go to the core admin page and hit the button.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Things will fail early with java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Path must not end with / character, but not before publishing a poison pill state to the overseer queue, which leads into further issues due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5811&quot; title=&quot;The Overseer will retry work items until success.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13921097" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2014 17:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1574589 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=markrmiller%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;markrmiller@gmail.com&quot;&gt;markrmiller@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;dev/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1574589&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1574589&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5813&quot; title=&quot;Creating a SolrCore with a collection name of empty string should fail nicely in SolrCloud mode.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5813&quot;&gt;SOLR-5813&lt;/a&gt;: tests for &quot;&quot; or null collection name - should default to core name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13921101" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2014 17:50:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; I was looking at a slightly older version of Solr and I think part of this issue was already addressed (though &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5811&quot; title=&quot;The Overseer will retry work items until success.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-5811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; could also improve the behaviour here).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For some reason, previously, it seems that a collection name of &quot;&quot; would end up as a valid name, and now it gets treated as no collection and you get the default core name for the collection as if it was null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, I&apos;ve added a couple tests for null or &quot;&quot; collection names and will dig around a bit more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13921102" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 5 Mar 2014 17:50:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1574590 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=markrmiller%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;markrmiller@gmail.com&quot;&gt;markrmiller@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;dev/branches/branch_4x&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1574590&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1574590&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-5813&quot; title=&quot;Creating a SolrCore with a collection name of empty string should fail nicely in SolrCloud mode.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-5813&quot;&gt;SOLR-5813&lt;/a&gt;: tests for &quot;&quot; or null collection name - should default to core name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13971161" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 12:57:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Move issue to Solr 4.9.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
